IT ORDERS to buy at 1,380-1,400 zone             │\n│  4. SET TARGET SELL at 1,500 if reached without breakout     │\n│  5. TIGHTEN stops to 1,350 on all positions                   │\n│  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────  │\n│  Key Catalysts to Watch:                                      │\n│  • Q1 2025 Earnings (April 2025)                             │\n│  • Jiang Yan investigation resolution                         │\n│  •能否突破1,500 (Can it break 1,500?)                         │\n│  • Sector inflow/outflow data                                 │\n│  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────  │\n│  Expected Range (3-6 months): 1,350 - 1,550                  │\n│  Probability-Weighted Return: -5% to +10% over 6 months      │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## VI. THE BOTTOM LINE\n\n### What Both Sides Agree On:\n\n1. **Moutai is an exceptional business** — the brand, margins, and balance sheet are genuinely world-class\n2. **The stock is not cheap** — current valuation requires continued outperformance\n3. **The 1,470-1,500 zone is critical** — this is the make-or-break level\n4. **Governance uncertainty is real** — but unlikely to destroy the business\n5. **The next 60-90 days are pivotal** — MACD signal and earnings will clarify direction\n\n### Where They Disagree:\n\n1. **Is the MACD golden cross real?** Bulls say yes; Bears say false signal\n2. **Will Chinese consumers keep spending?** Bulls say yes; Bears say no\n3. **Is 20x P/E justified?** Bulls say yes; Bears say 15-18x is fair\n\n### The Moderator\'s Final Word:\n\n**This is a stock for patient, long-term investors who can withstand 10-20% volatility.** Short-term traders will find better risk/reward elsewhere. Value investors should wait for better entry points.\n\nThe bulls are right that this is a generational business. The bears are right that generational businesses can still decline 20-30% when priced for perfect