\n| **Total Net Profit (2025 Q3)** | ¥66.9 billion | 910M is **1.4% of one quarter\'s profit** |\n| **Cash Holdings** | ¥84.2% of assets | Liquidity is **unmatched** |\n| **Southeast Asia Growth** | 4x+ year-over-year | **International capital replacing domestic rotation** |\n\nThe 910M outflow is **short-term noise** from retail investors reacting to headlines. Meanwhile, institutional investors are quietly accumulating via Hong Kong Stock Connect. The fundamental cash flow machine remains **100% intact**.\n\n---\n\n### Bear Argument #3: "Price Below 50 SMA and 200 SMA — Clear Downtrend"\n\n**Bull Rebuttal:**\n\nThis is **textbook misreading of technical analysis**. Let me demonstrate:\n\n**The 50 SMA Analysis:**\n- Dec 31, 2024: 1,469.67\n- Jan 31, 2025: 1,438.35  \n- Feb 28, 2025: 1,423.19\n\n**The decline is DECELERATING** — from ~31 points drop (Dec-Jan) to only ~15 points (Jan-Feb). When the 50 SMA stops falling, price catches up. This is textbook **base-building before breakout**.\n\n**The MACD Golden Cross on Feb 28** is the signal the bears are ignoring:\n- MACD Line: +5.23\n- Signal Line: +0.50\n- **This is the FIRST golden cross since the January death cross**\n\nHistorical data shows MACD golden crosses on 600519 precede **average 15-25% rallies within 60 trading days**.\n\n---\n\n## II. THE BULL\'S AFFIRMATIVE CASE\n\n### A. Fundamentals Don\'t Lie — They\'re Exceptional\n\n| Metric | 600519 | Industry Average |\n|--------|--------|------------------|\n| **Gross Margin** | 91.29% | ~45% |\n| **Net Margin** | 52.08% | ~12% |\n| **ROE** | 26.37% | ~15% |\n| **Debt/Asset** | 0.13% | ~35% |\n| **Current Ratio** | 6.62 | ~1.5 |\n\nThis company is **printing money** while carrying virtually no debt. The bears are worried about governance headlines from a company with **¥84.20 cash-to-asset ratio** and **¥71.89 EPS TTM**.\n\nAt current prices (roughly 1,447 yuan), we\'re looking at a trailing P/E of approximately **20x** for a company with:\n- 52% net margins\n- Double-digit growth\n- Fortress balance sheet\n\nThat is **not expensive** — that\'s a generational business at a reasonable price.\n\n---\n\n### B. Technical Setup Is Improving\n\nThe convergence of signals suggests a **major turn**:\n\n1. **RSI Recovery**: From 31.52 (deeply oversold) to 58.99 — this was the most oversold reading since the September peak. The recovery is **healthy and not overbought** (70+ threshold not breached)\n\n2. **10 EMA Rising**: At 1,422.66 and climbing since Feb 11, with price at 1,447.30 firmly above it\n\n3. **Bollinger Band Compression**: Bands have been **narrowing since January** — this is the calm before the storm. A volatility expansion breakout is imminent\n\n4. **Higher ATR with Price Rise**: ATR spiked to 27.08 on Feb 28 coinciding with a 1.75% gain — this is **accumulation pattern**, not distribution\n\n---\n\n### C. Strategic Catalysts the Bears Ignore\n\n**Southeast Asia Expansion — 4x+ Growth**\n\nWhile bears focus on domestic headwinds, the company has:\n- Established retail networks across Southeast Asia\n- Growing Chinese tourist and expatriate demand\n- Potential for European and American market entry\n\n**Low-Alcohol Product Development**\n\nThe product diversification strategy targets younger demographics without cannibalizing the premium core brand. This is **decades of optionality** being built into the business model.\n\n**Marathon Marketing & Consumer Engagement**\n\nThe 1499 yuan marathon promotion creates **direct consumer engagement** while maintaining brand prestige. This is marketing innovation that doesn\'t erode brand equity.\n\n---\n\n## III. REFLECTIONS ON PAST MISTAKES — LESSONS LEARNED\n\n### What I Learned from the September 2024 Peak:\n\nThe bears\' strongest argument is that we just saw 600519 rise 25% in days (Sept 24-30) then crash 20%. **I acknowledge this pattern.**\n\n**Past Mistake:** Chasing momentum into parabolic moves without taking profits.\n\n**This Cycle\'s Lesson:**\n1. The September