e 1,470-1,500 zone is critical** — this is the make-or-break level\n4. **Governance uncertainty is real** — but unlikely to destroy the business\n5. **The next 60-90 days are pivotal** — MACD signal and earnings will clarify direction\n\n### Where They Disagree:\n\n1. **Is the MACD golden cross real?** Bulls say yes; Bears say false signal\n2. **Will Chinese consumers keep spending?** Bulls say yes; Bears say no\n3. **Is 20x P/E justified?** Bulls say yes; Bears say 15-18x is fair\n\n### The Moderator\'s Final Word:\n\n**This is a stock for patient, long-term investors who can withstand 10-20% volatility.** Short-term traders will find better risk/reward elsewhere. Value investors should wait for better entry points.\n\nThe bulls are right that this is a generational business. The bears are right that generational businesses can still decline 20-30% when priced for perfection.\n\n**My recommendation: Neutral with a slight defensive tilt. Hold positions, don\'t add aggressively, and wait for either a pullback to 1,380 or a confirmed break above 1,500 before changing strategy.**\n\n---\n\n## VII. IMPORTANT DISCLAIMER\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    ⚠️ IMPORTANT NOTICE ⚠️                    │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  This analysis is provided for EDUCATIONAL and INFORMATIONAL│\n│  purposes only. It does not constitute financial advice.    │\n│                                                              │\n│  • This is a DEBATE FORMAT presenting multiple perspectives │\n│  • Past performance does not guarantee future results        │\n│  • Technical analysis has inherent limitations              │\n│  • Fundamental analysis requires assumptions about future   │\n│  • Market conditions can change rapidly and unexpectedly    │\n│                                                              │\n│  Before making investment decisions:                          │\n│  1. Co