ed break above 1,500\n- **Aggressive traders:** Small long position with tight stop at 1,420, target 1,480\n\n### Key Catalysts to Watch:\n- Q1 2025 Earnings (April 2025)\n- Jiang Yan investigation resolution\n-能否突破1,500 (Can it break 1,500?)\n- Volume confirmation on any breakout\n\n---\n\n## Risk/Reward Analysis\n\n| Scenario | Probability | Price Target | Action |\n|----------|-------------|--------------|--------|\n| **Bull Case** (Break above 1,500) | 25% | 1,600-1,700 | Add on breakout |\n| **Base Case** (Range bound) | 50% | 1,400-1,480 | Trade range |\n| **Bear Case** (Test 1,350-1,380) | 25% | 1,300-1,350 | Accumulate on dip |\n\n---\n\n## Learning from This Analysis\n\nThe key insight from this Moutai analysis is that **quality alone does not justify valuation**. Even the world\'s best liquor business needs a reasonable entry price to generate acceptable returns. The bulls correctly identified the exceptional business fundamentals, but the bears correctly identified that **paying 20x P/E for decelerating growth leaves little margin of safety**.\n\n**Lesson for future trades:** In uncertain macro environments with governance risks, demand a larger margin of safety before buying even exceptional businesses. The best business at the wrong price is not an investment, it\'s speculation.\n\n---\n\n**FINAL TRANSACTION PROPOSAL: HOLD**', 'risk_debate_state': {'judge_decision': '<think>\nThe user wants me to act as a "Wise Moderator" in a trading debate about 600519 Kweichow Moutai. I need to:\n\n1. Analyze both the aggressive analyst\'s (bullish) and conservative analyst\'s (bearish/neutral) arguments\n2. Challenge both perspectives critically\n3. Find the balanced middle ground\n4. Make an actionable recommendation with detailed reasoning\n5. Include past reflections ("learn from past mistakes")\n6. Deliver clear BUY/SELL/HOLD recommendation with detailed reasoning\n\nLet me analyze the key points from both sides and find where they went wrong or oversimplified.\