viction.\n\n---\n\n## My Trading Decision\n\n**Target Entry Zone:** 1,420-1,440 (current levels)\n\n**Stop-Loss:** 1,350 (below recent consolidation floor)\n\n**Upside Targets:**\n- Near-term: 1,480 (upper range boundary)\n- Medium-term: 1,520-1,550 (breakout confirmation)\n- Long-term: 1,600+ (revisit all-time highs)\n\n**Position Sizing:** Aggressive entry with 8-10% portfolio allocation given the risk/reward asymmetry.\n\n---\n\n## Why Risk-Taking Wins Here\n\nThe conservative analyst wants you to wait for perfect conditions that *never* arrive. The neutral analyst offers tepid "range trade" advice that leaves money on the table. But here\'s the reality:\n\n1. **The MACD golden cross is a statistically significant momentum shift**—history shows these generate above-average returns over the next 3-6 months.\n\n2. **RSI recovery without overbought readings means there\'s room to run**—we\'re not late to this move.\n\n3. **Moutai\'s fundamentals justify holding through volatility**—even if there\'s a short-term pullback, the business quality ensures recovery.\n\n4. **Waiting for "confirmed breakout" above 1,500 means buying at worse risk/reward**—you\'ll face more resistance and narrower margins.\n\nThe market is offering you a chance to accumulate shares of the world\'s most profitable liquor business at a discount to its true value. The governance concerns are temporary. The brand is permanent. The fundamentals are pristine.\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion\n\nEvery great trade requires conviction when others are uncertain. Right now, uncertainty around Moutai stems from short-term noise, not structural concerns. The technicals are aligning, the fundamentals are exceptional, and sentiment is cautiously pessimistic—*textbook* contrarian entry conditions.\n\nThe conservative approach of waiting guarantees lower risk but also guarantees lower returns. The neutral approach of range-trading misses the multi-month趋势 that follows momentum shifts like the one we\'re witnessing *to